race.comment: A few strong form lines converge. GENEROUS HARRY (2) returned from a 13-month absence last start with a decisive win over this distance at Wyong, taking charge before the bend then going right on with it. The one to beat again if that run hasn't gassed him - keep a close eye on the market late. Promising filly DIETRICH (10) resumed with a tidy win in a maiden over this course and distance last time out. That was a career-high figure so she is on the ascendancy. Perfectly drawn to play a significant role again. SEA ADMIRAL (4) led from the outset to easily take out a Class 1 over this journey at Nowra when fresh from a spell recently. Tougher task this time but he has only raced four times and has a stack of upside. A couple of things went wrong for DEFIANT HEART (1) at Warwick Farm last time. Loves racing here and can bounce back. PRINCESS CRUIZER (6) has not raced for seven weeks so might need this, but a top four finish would not shock.
